      "content": "i feel like \"challenging the dominant narrative\" is just a fancy way of saying it's becoming biased. if schools are trying to be \"accurate\" like you said, shouldn't they be sticking to the established facts instead of focusing so much on these new perspectives that make people upset? isn't there a risk that being \"inclusive\" actually just means making the history less objective?",
